<p itemprop="description">Machine learning involves developing and applying algorithms and statistical models that enable computer systems to learn and improve from experience to solve complex problems and make predictions.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand machine learning concepts and applications, and recognise opportunities where machine learning could benefit government services.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can apply basic machine learning techniques using standard tools and libraries, and contribute to machine learning projects under guidance.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can design and implement machine learning solutions, select appropriate algorithms, and manage the full machine learning lifecycle from data to deployment.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can lead machine learning strategy, develop innovative ML solutions for complex government challenges, and establish machine learning capabilities across organizations.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

